WEBVTT

00:02.122 --> 00:03.703
[straining]

00:03.803 --> 00:05.105
- I still can't believe
this is happening.

00:05.205 --> 00:06.826
- Oh, it's happening.

00:06.926 --> 00:08.468
- I used to love the
Sacramento Children's Theater

00:08.568 --> 00:09.950
when I was a kid.

00:10.050 --> 00:11.871
If only little
theater dork Sarah

00:11.971 --> 00:14.314
knew that one day they
would be putting on her play,

00:14.414 --> 00:16.636
"Unsung Sheroes."

00:16.736 --> 00:17.797
What?

00:17.897 --> 00:18.758
- Usually you say
the full title.

00:18.858 --> 00:20.360
- "A Musical Celebration

00:20.460 --> 00:21.421
of Groundbreaking Women
from Sacagawea to Sotomayor"?

00:21.501 --> 00:22.802
We don't have time for that.

00:22.902 --> 00:25.445
Oh, did I pack Greta Thunberg's
raincoat?

00:25.545 --> 00:27.087
- Yes. It's with
Joan Jett's leather pants

00:27.187 --> 00:28.688
and Jane Fonda's leotard.
- Okay.

00:28.788 --> 00:30.370
Ready?

00:30.470 --> 00:32.692
Go, go, go, go, go, go, go,
go, go, go, go, go, go.

00:32.792 --> 00:34.534
[laughing]
Okay.

00:34.634 --> 00:36.336
- I'm gonna miss you.
- I'm gonna miss you.

00:36.436 --> 00:37.857
But I'll be back
for Christmas.

00:37.957 --> 00:39.779
Maybe sooner if staying
with my parents

00:39.879 --> 00:41.541
drives me absolutely insane.

00:41.641 --> 00:43.063
- Well, you're welcome
to be here instead

00:43.163 --> 00:44.424
when my parents come visit.

00:44.524 --> 00:46.546
- I'm actually bummed
I'm gonna miss them.

00:46.646 --> 00:47.947
- That's because
they're on their best behaviour

00:48.047 --> 00:49.109
when you're around.

00:49.209 --> 00:50.750
Otherwise,
they never stop arguing.

00:50.850 --> 00:52.192
They are the only people

00:52.292 --> 00:53.953
to get kicked out of
a Jimmy Buffett concert

00:54.053 --> 00:56.556
for literally fighting over
a cheeseburger in paradise.

00:56.656 --> 00:58.358
- Okay.

00:58.458 --> 00:59.919
Do you want me to cancel?

01:00.019 --> 01:01.921
Because if you do,
just say the word and I will.

01:02.021 --> 01:03.083
- No, I'll be fine.

01:03.183 --> 01:04.324
- Okay, great.

01:04.424 --> 01:05.605
Because you know,
I got time off from work

01:05.705 --> 01:07.807
and packing all this stuff
was just a lot.

01:07.907 --> 01:09.209
Aw!

01:09.309 --> 01:11.091
- Oh, we didn't pack
Dolly Parton's wig.

01:11.191 --> 01:13.933
- Oh, that's okay.
I'll just wear it in the car.

01:14.033 --> 01:15.575
Pulling it off?

01:15.675 --> 01:16.816
- Yeah.

01:16.916 --> 01:18.978
[laughter]

01:19.078 --> 01:22.142
[glass clinking]

01:22.242 --> 01:23.903
- Hear me, hear me.

01:24.003 --> 01:25.905
- Actually, it's "ye."

01:26.005 --> 01:27.307
- Who the hell is ye?

01:27.407 --> 01:28.228
- You know, yeah,
just keep going.

01:28.328 --> 01:30.750
- A toast to Tom Hayworth

01:30.850 --> 01:34.394
on making "The New York Times"
Best Seller list.

01:34.494 --> 01:36.396
- Ah, it's not that big a deal.
It's only number nine.

01:36.496 --> 01:37.637
- It is a big deal.

01:37.737 --> 01:38.638
- I know.
It's a huge deal!

01:38.738 --> 01:39.799
Number nine, baby!
Whoo!

01:39.899 --> 01:41.041
I did it!
[all cheer]

01:41.141 --> 01:42.482
It is so strange knowing

01:42.582 --> 01:44.244
how we're gonna
pay the mortgage this month.

01:44.344 --> 01:46.926
What is this odd sensation
that I'm having?

01:47.026 --> 01:49.129
- Could it be
that you're happy?

01:49.229 --> 01:50.490
- Is this what that feels like?

01:50.590 --> 01:51.931
- Hey,
are you around this week?

01:52.031 --> 01:53.653
I could use some backup
with my parents.

01:53.753 --> 01:55.615
- Oh, I'm sorry.
I know they're a handful.

01:55.715 --> 01:57.177
I'm just really busy at work.

01:57.277 --> 01:58.498
- Oh, did you get a design job?

01:58.598 --> 02:00.980
- I wish.
Dumb law stuff at the firm.

02:01.080 --> 02:03.583
I turned down a chance
to design a billiard room.

02:03.683 --> 02:04.904
- Like in "Clue"?

02:05.004 --> 02:07.147
- Yes.
Imagine all the murders.

02:07.247 --> 02:09.189
- Well, you could always
swing by my slice of paradise.

02:09.289 --> 02:10.870
I think your parents are cool.

02:10.970 --> 02:13.433
And Jimmy
is my second-favourite Buffett.

02:13.533 --> 02:15.075
Behind Warren, of course.
- Thanks.

02:15.175 --> 02:16.756
But are you sure?

02:16.856 --> 02:18.798
Now that they're retired,
they have more energy to argue.

02:18.898 --> 02:21.481
- Denise, come on.
We're practically family.

02:21.581 --> 02:22.682
I dated your sister.

02:22.782 --> 02:25.044
I could have been
your brother-in-law.

02:25.144 --> 02:26.606
- You are my brother-in-law.

02:26.706 --> 02:28.808
- Thanks. That's really sweet
of you to say.

02:28.908 --> 02:31.251
[upbeat music]

02:31.351 --> 02:33.673
- ♪ Hey, hey, hey, hey! ♪

02:37.917 --> 02:40.620
- Huh.

02:40.720 --> 02:44.104
Honey, did Connor
give the twins cash again?

02:44.204 --> 02:46.586
[smooth R&B music]

02:46.686 --> 02:48.268
Oh, this is sex cash.

02:48.368 --> 02:49.709
- Remember?

02:49.809 --> 02:51.271
We said if you made it
to the Best Sellers list,

02:51.371 --> 02:52.832
we'd have sex
on the stacks of cash

02:52.932 --> 02:54.594
like a couple of bank robbers?

02:54.694 --> 02:57.117
- And you agreed because you
assumed it would never happen?

02:57.217 --> 02:58.958
- Well, it was either this
or the other thing,

02:59.058 --> 03:00.560
and I am never
doing the other thing.

03:00.660 --> 03:02.802
- [chuckles] It's gonna be
so much better than last year

03:02.902 --> 03:04.684
when we had to do this
on a single paycheque.

03:04.784 --> 03:06.726
- I felt so dirty cashing it.
- Did you?

03:06.826 --> 03:12.292
♪ ♪

03:12.392 --> 03:14.053
- Tom?
- Mm-hmm?

03:14.153 --> 03:16.015
- You okay?
- Yeah, I'm okay.

03:16.115 --> 03:18.298
- You thinking about our
getaway driver who got caught?

03:18.398 --> 03:19.459
Don't worry.

03:19.559 --> 03:21.901
It just means more dinero
for us.

03:22.001 --> 03:24.824
- [chuckles] Seeing all this
cash laid out here like this--

03:24.924 --> 03:27.026
- Yeah, I know.
It's a little gross.

03:27.126 --> 03:30.390
I really was hoping they'd
give us new dollar bills, but--

03:30.490 --> 03:31.831
maybe we could put a sheet
on top.

03:31.931 --> 03:33.393
- No.

03:33.493 --> 03:35.315
Well, yeah, probably just--
this is very gross.

03:35.415 --> 03:37.317
But...
[sighs]

03:37.417 --> 03:39.279
What if this is it for me?
- Oh, God.

03:39.379 --> 03:41.921
- No, I mean, what if my career
has reached its peak?

03:42.021 --> 03:44.404
- And...11 hours.

03:44.504 --> 03:45.645
- What?

03:45.745 --> 03:48.127
- You managed
11 hours of happiness

03:48.227 --> 03:49.729
before you started to worry.

03:49.829 --> 03:52.252
- I'm not worried, I'm--
oh, my God.

03:52.352 --> 03:53.853
Oh, my God,
what if I'm worried?

03:53.953 --> 03:55.855
- Tom, you got
on the Best Sellers list.

03:55.955 --> 03:58.698
That is a big deal!
You should be ecstatic!

03:58.798 --> 04:01.301
I'm still glowing from
redecorating Gretchen's room,

04:01.401 --> 04:03.263
and that was two months ago.

04:03.363 --> 04:05.825
You should do something
to savour this moment.

04:05.925 --> 04:08.147
- You mean like
see a magic show?

04:08.247 --> 04:09.669
I guess there's
this new close-up guy

04:09.769 --> 04:11.671
who's doing some
pretty innovative stuff

04:11.771 --> 04:13.032
with cups and balls.

04:13.132 --> 04:15.755
- Or you could grab
some of this gross money,

04:15.855 --> 04:17.437
which has sunscreen on it.

04:17.537 --> 04:19.359
Oh, I hope that's sunscreen.
- Okay.

04:19.459 --> 04:21.961
- And buy something
to celebrate.

04:22.061 --> 04:23.483
- Yeah, you know what?
I'm gonna do it.

04:23.583 --> 04:25.445
Right after
I see that magic show.

04:25.545 --> 04:26.806
Or no,
instead of the magic show.

04:26.906 --> 04:28.848
That's better.
[chuckles]

04:28.948 --> 04:31.611
So, uh, should we still...

04:31.711 --> 04:32.892
- I think we need
to burn the sheets.

04:32.992 --> 04:34.294
- Oh, thank God.
[groans softly]

04:34.394 --> 04:35.415
♪ ♪

04:35.515 --> 04:37.056
- Mom, Dad,

04:37.156 --> 04:39.058
the constant bickering
has to stop.

04:39.158 --> 04:40.580
It's toxic.

04:40.680 --> 04:42.222
No, no, let me finish.

04:42.322 --> 04:43.823
It's infecting
your relationship with me

04:43.923 --> 04:45.925
and my kids, okay?

04:47.206 --> 04:49.068
- Oh, just stop it, Jay!
- No, you stop it!

04:49.168 --> 04:50.470
- [sighs]
- Oh, you couldn't take--

04:50.570 --> 04:52.352
- I hope they take it
as well as you did.

04:52.452 --> 04:54.073
- Woman,
I'm just getting started!

04:54.173 --> 04:55.835
- [groans]

04:55.935 --> 04:57.016
You two aren't even in the
apartment and you're already...

04:57.096 --> 04:58.318
[laughter]

04:58.418 --> 05:00.480
Hugging?
- Denise!

05:00.580 --> 05:02.802
Your father is so hilarious.
He just told me a joke.

05:02.902 --> 05:04.244
It's like I'm living
with Steve Harvey.

05:04.344 --> 05:06.606
- Oh, no, no, no, no.
He is much funnier.

05:06.706 --> 05:07.727
Oh!

05:07.827 --> 05:09.249
But hey,
I do look good in a suit!

05:09.349 --> 05:10.610
[laughter]

05:10.710 --> 05:13.092
- Wow, look at you two,
getting along.

05:13.192 --> 05:16.095
- Yeah, yeah, we are just
so happy to see you.

05:16.195 --> 05:17.937
- Yes.
- And our grandbabies.

05:18.037 --> 05:19.859
Where's Kelvin?
Does he have a moustache yet?

05:19.959 --> 05:21.261
And if not, why not?

05:21.361 --> 05:22.742
- They are on their way back
from the park.

05:22.842 --> 05:24.063
both: Mm.
- But we can get you settled.

05:24.163 --> 05:25.465
You two can sleep
in my bedroom,

05:25.565 --> 05:26.906
and I will sleep on the couch.

05:27.006 --> 05:28.107
- Ah.
- Oh, no need.

05:28.207 --> 05:29.989
We're just gonna stay
in the RV.

05:30.089 --> 05:31.431
- What RV?

05:31.531 --> 05:32.472
- After we sold
our dental practice,

05:32.572 --> 05:34.073
then we bought an RV.

05:34.173 --> 05:36.636
You might say it's our...
- Wait for it.

05:36.736 --> 05:38.758
- Molar home.
[both laugh]

05:38.858 --> 05:40.440
- I told you.
It's like he's Steve Harvey.

05:40.540 --> 05:41.641
I told you!
- Oh, no, no, no, no.

05:41.741 --> 05:43.002
Steve RV.

05:43.102 --> 05:44.844
- Uh-uh! You are so bad!
- Huh? Huh? [laughs]

05:44.944 --> 05:46.406
- [chuckles dryly]
Very bad.

05:46.506 --> 05:48.848
[both laughing]
- Anyway, yeah, yeah, yeah.

05:48.948 --> 05:52.372
We drove it all the way
from Tampa Bay.

05:52.472 --> 05:54.694
- You chose
to drive cross-country

05:54.794 --> 05:56.215
in a confined space together?

05:56.315 --> 05:57.977
- Oh, RV life is so fun.

05:58.077 --> 05:59.659
It's like we're on
a non-stop vacation.

05:59.759 --> 06:01.301
- Mm-hmm.

06:01.401 --> 06:03.142
- Our vacations were the worst.
You two always fought.

06:03.242 --> 06:04.944
- Oh, Denise,
you're exaggerating.

06:05.044 --> 06:06.185
- We're banned
from Spirit Airlines,

06:06.285 --> 06:08.287
and they need customers.

06:09.248 --> 06:10.750
- Hey, honey.

06:10.850 --> 06:13.313
I took your advice on enjoying
the fruits of my success,

06:13.413 --> 06:14.634
and I did it.

06:14.734 --> 06:16.796
I actually
bought myself something.

06:16.896 --> 06:19.319
- That's great,
but I've had a long day.

06:19.419 --> 06:21.521
Could I see your R2-D2

06:21.621 --> 06:24.083
or wearable Hobbit feet
or whatever later?

06:24.183 --> 06:25.445
- I got something even better.
Come on.

06:25.545 --> 06:26.606
I gotta show you right now.
Sorry. Come on.

06:26.706 --> 06:28.328
[lively island music]

06:28.428 --> 06:31.050
Ta-da!

06:31.150 --> 06:32.492
- You bought a hot tub?

06:32.592 --> 06:34.293
- I did.
I bought a hot tub.

06:34.393 --> 06:36.576
Always wanted one,
now I got one.

06:36.676 --> 06:37.857
- I'm surprised.

06:37.957 --> 06:39.619
Hot tub doesn't exactly
scream, "Tom."

06:39.719 --> 06:41.260
- Yeah, I know.

06:41.360 --> 06:42.782
But growing up, our next-door
neighbours had a hot tub,

06:42.882 --> 06:45.345
and I was always so jealous
listening to them

06:45.445 --> 06:47.667
soaking in the tub
and popping Frescas.

06:47.767 --> 06:48.908
Always sounded like

06:49.008 --> 06:51.070
they were having such a blast,
you know?

06:51.170 --> 06:52.832
So I think they did a lot
of hardcore drugs.

06:52.932 --> 06:54.594
All right, you want to take
this bad boy out for a spin?

06:54.694 --> 06:55.835
- Hells yeah.

06:55.935 --> 06:57.557
I choose to jacuzz.
- Yeah.

06:57.657 --> 06:59.038
- I'm gonna put on
my bathing suit!

06:59.138 --> 07:01.200
- I'm gonna pop a Fresca!

07:01.300 --> 07:03.523
[Fresca pops]

07:03.623 --> 07:04.764
Oh, boy.

07:04.864 --> 07:07.527
[chuckling]
That's a little spicy.

07:07.627 --> 07:10.329
- Ultimately, it's about
taking responsibility,

07:10.429 --> 07:13.212
about accepting the blame
for your actions.

07:13.312 --> 07:16.896
Until you do that,
you'll always be adrift.

07:16.996 --> 07:18.938
Anyways, that's what I think
"Margaritaville" is about.

07:19.038 --> 07:20.259
both: Mm.

07:20.359 --> 07:22.221
- That's a great
interpretation, Connor.

07:22.321 --> 07:24.263
- It is so nice
to see people your age

07:24.363 --> 07:26.225
getting into real music.

07:26.325 --> 07:28.027
- Yeah.

07:28.127 --> 07:30.269
- Look, look--what are your
thoughts on "Jamaica Mistaica"?

07:30.369 --> 07:32.632
- I think we've covered enough
of Jimmy Buffett's catalogue.

07:32.732 --> 07:34.273
- Can I tell you
the chicken is just amazing?

07:34.373 --> 07:35.995
I have eaten every bite.

07:36.095 --> 07:37.517
- Oh, here, baby.
You can have a piece of mine.

07:37.617 --> 07:39.078
- Oh, thank you.
- Absolutely.

07:39.178 --> 07:41.200
Here you go there.
- Mm. [chuckles]

07:41.300 --> 07:42.181
- You know,
there's more in the kitchen,

07:42.261 --> 07:43.883
so you can just stop that.

07:43.983 --> 07:45.084
[both laughing]
- Oh, you got me.

07:45.184 --> 07:46.806
- [chuckles]
- And Connor,

07:46.906 --> 07:49.088
your place
is even nicer than JoJo said.

07:49.188 --> 07:51.330
- How is JoJo, by the way?
- Oh, she is great.

07:51.430 --> 07:54.133
You know she's gonna be on
"Influencer Lagoon All-Stars"?

07:54.233 --> 07:55.895
- Yeah, think she's got
a real shot to win it too,

07:55.995 --> 07:58.217
if she takes down that D'Amelio
sister from season--

07:58.317 --> 08:00.339
[clears throat]
I mean I watch sports.

08:00.439 --> 08:01.521
[chuckling] I don't watch
that kind of stuff.

08:01.601 --> 08:02.662
- [chuckling]
Oh. Huh.

08:02.762 --> 08:04.704
- You two were
such a cute couple.

08:04.804 --> 08:06.065
You seeing anyone now?

08:06.165 --> 08:09.549
- No, but I'm out there.
You know, on the apps.

08:09.649 --> 08:10.950
The dating apps.

08:11.050 --> 08:13.072
Kinda like going to a bar,
but on your phone.

08:13.172 --> 08:14.393
- We know what apps are.

08:14.493 --> 08:15.555
I mean, we're old,
but we're not that old.

08:15.655 --> 08:16.756
[both laugh]

08:16.856 --> 08:17.757
- I am just so grateful that

08:17.857 --> 08:20.239
I met Jay
the old-fashioned way.

08:20.339 --> 08:23.322
- Her father's horse
kicked my car.

08:23.422 --> 08:24.764
Remember that?
- That was the day.

08:24.864 --> 08:26.125
- That was the day.
[chuckles]

08:26.225 --> 08:28.127
- They seem really happy.

08:28.227 --> 08:29.689
- I know.

08:29.789 --> 08:32.932
And I'm gonna get
to the bottom of it.

08:33.032 --> 08:35.214
- Ay-yi-yi.
- Oh, yeah.

08:35.314 --> 08:36.856
It's nice, right?
- Mm!

08:36.956 --> 08:39.258
- Actually, it's a little loud.

08:39.358 --> 08:40.700
[electronic beep]
There we go.

08:40.800 --> 08:44.183
- This might be the best idea
you have ever had.

08:44.283 --> 08:45.384
- Well, you're the one
who talked me into

08:45.484 --> 08:46.746
spending it myself, so.

08:46.846 --> 08:48.027
- That's right.

08:48.127 --> 08:49.629
This is the best idea
I've ever had.

08:49.729 --> 08:50.950
- [chuckles]

08:51.050 --> 08:54.754
Mm! Feel that heat.
104 on the dot.

08:54.854 --> 08:57.436
- It's perfect.
- Fantastic.

08:57.536 --> 08:59.719
It's a little chlorine-y,
though, right?

08:59.819 --> 09:02.161
- No, I think it smells fine.
- Okay, cool.

09:02.261 --> 09:04.443
Water's a little hard, though.
- What? Hard?

09:04.543 --> 09:06.205
- No, I'm just saying we should
probably use a softener.

09:06.305 --> 09:07.807
It's like a pH thing.

09:07.907 --> 09:09.649
- The water feels like water.

09:09.749 --> 09:11.811
Maybe you should just,
you know, enjoy it.

09:11.911 --> 09:13.332
- Totally.

09:13.432 --> 09:16.395
Let the hot tub take the wheel.
- Yeah. [sighs]

09:17.717 --> 09:18.858
What is it?
- What?

09:18.958 --> 09:20.580
Nothing, nothing.
[chuckles]

09:20.680 --> 09:22.261
Just the electric meter's
going crazy.

09:22.361 --> 09:24.303
Didn't really think about what
this'll do to our power bill.

09:24.403 --> 09:27.346
- Okay, let's swap places.
- Okay.

09:27.446 --> 09:29.148
How's this gonna
help lower our bill?

09:29.248 --> 09:31.030
- It'll prevent you
from seeing the meter.

09:31.130 --> 09:32.311
- Right.

09:32.411 --> 09:34.514
Well, this is perfect.

09:34.614 --> 09:36.235
Whoo!
Tub life!

09:36.335 --> 09:37.597
- Mm.

09:37.697 --> 09:38.878
- Okay, I can see
into Mrs. Kim's house.

09:38.978 --> 09:40.439
And if I can see her,
then she can see me.

09:40.539 --> 09:42.882
- Mrs. Kim is not looking
at you.

09:42.982 --> 09:45.324
Can you please focus?
We're in a hot tub!

09:45.424 --> 09:48.167
I'm wearing a swimsuit.
Do the math.

09:48.267 --> 09:50.770
- Oh.
Yeah, well...

09:50.870 --> 09:53.713
math was always one
of my favourite subjects.

09:54.874 --> 09:56.976
Oh, you gotta be kidding me.

09:57.076 --> 09:58.778
- Tom!
- Got a dead bee.

09:58.878 --> 10:00.459
Got a dead bee in here.
Don't worry, I got it.

10:00.559 --> 10:01.821
Whoa, I don't got it!
It's alive.

10:01.921 --> 10:03.222
It is very much alive!

10:03.322 --> 10:04.403
We might be dealing
with a murder hornet here.

10:04.483 --> 10:05.625
I'm gonna go get a knife.

10:05.725 --> 10:07.667
- Right behind you.

10:07.767 --> 10:10.630
[quirky upbeat music]

10:10.730 --> 10:12.752
♪ ♪

10:12.852 --> 10:14.473
[laughter]
- Who thought of that?

10:14.573 --> 10:15.915
- Okay, enough.

10:16.015 --> 10:17.436
You two are usually
at each other's throats

10:17.536 --> 10:19.518
and now you're all sweet
and affectionate.

10:19.618 --> 10:22.201
It's too much.
What is going on?

10:22.301 --> 10:25.004
- Well, if you must know...

10:25.104 --> 10:27.406
your father and I have been
seeing a couples therapist.

10:27.506 --> 10:29.528
- We're learning to listen
to each other's needs

10:29.628 --> 10:31.010
and be more flexible.
- Mm-hmm.

10:31.110 --> 10:32.371
- Couples therapy.

10:32.471 --> 10:33.973
Sarah's gonna be so mad
she missed this.

10:34.073 --> 10:35.054
- Judith--
that's our therapist...

10:35.154 --> 10:36.375
- Yeah.

10:36.475 --> 10:38.938
- She taught us all about
savouring life.

10:39.038 --> 10:40.339
Speaking of,

10:40.439 --> 10:43.142
there is a gorgeous bridge
out there

10:43.242 --> 10:46.505
that I would love to stare at
with a gorgeous lady.

10:46.605 --> 10:48.748
- Survey says
you're talking about me.

10:48.848 --> 10:50.509
[both laugh]
- Come on.

10:50.609 --> 10:53.192
- Oh, yes.
Thank you.

10:53.292 --> 10:55.194
- Watch yourself.
- Okay. Thank you.

10:55.294 --> 10:56.395
- Maybe they
really have changed.

10:56.495 --> 10:57.837
- Yeah, cool, whatever.

10:57.937 --> 10:59.719
Hey, you really need
to see this profile.

10:59.819 --> 11:01.841
- Oh, Connor, I don't want
to see your dating apps.

11:01.941 --> 11:03.242
Let me guess.

11:03.342 --> 11:04.964
She likes "The Office"
and is pretty random.

11:05.064 --> 11:07.526
- I was swiping through
new singles in the area and...

11:07.626 --> 11:10.930
[sighs]
I came across this.

11:11.030 --> 11:13.492
- Huh. That thirsty lady
looks like my mom.

11:13.592 --> 11:15.334
Oh, that thirsty lady
is my mom.

11:15.434 --> 11:17.336
- Yeah. I don't have
an age setting on right now.

11:17.436 --> 11:19.438
I'm trying out some new stuff.

11:23.082 --> 11:25.144
- Oh, hey.
There you are.

11:25.244 --> 11:26.385
How was your walk?

11:26.485 --> 11:28.227
- Great.
Invigorating.

11:28.327 --> 11:30.830
- Okay, well,
the kids are already asleep

11:30.930 --> 11:32.832
and your father's
having a land shower.

11:32.932 --> 11:34.353
- A what?

11:34.453 --> 11:35.955
- That's what
we "RV people" call

11:36.055 --> 11:37.516
a shower inside of a building.

11:37.616 --> 11:39.118
Hey, are you okay?

11:39.218 --> 11:42.081
You were awfully quiet on
the drive back from Connor's.

11:42.181 --> 11:44.243
- I know what's going on.
You're cheating on Dad.

11:44.343 --> 11:45.805
- Cheating?
No.

11:45.905 --> 11:48.007
- Yes.
I saw you on Connor's app.

11:48.107 --> 11:50.409
He has no age setting
'cause he's trying some stuff.

11:50.509 --> 11:52.011
- Wait.
It's not what you think.

11:52.111 --> 11:53.532
- Oh, so I didn't see

11:53.632 --> 11:55.735
a profile pic of you
suggestively eating ice cream

11:55.835 --> 11:57.977
in a sweater I bought you
for Christmas?

11:58.077 --> 12:00.099
- Uh, okay, well,
it's partly what you think.

12:00.199 --> 12:01.661
- Ugh!
- But--oh.

12:01.761 --> 12:02.742
- I need a drink.

12:02.842 --> 12:04.103
- Hey, hey, hey, Tammy.

12:04.203 --> 12:06.625
I got a match that says
she's DTF.

12:06.725 --> 12:09.628
Now look, I also
Desire True Friendship,

12:09.728 --> 12:11.110
but does that mean that
she doesn't wanna--

12:11.210 --> 12:12.551
- No, no, no, no, no.
Jay, Jay.

12:12.651 --> 12:14.353
[chuckles]

12:14.453 --> 12:17.636
- What is happening?

12:17.736 --> 12:19.959
- Oh, h-hey, Denise.

12:20.059 --> 12:21.440
How was your walk?

12:21.540 --> 12:23.362
- Honey, this is what
I'm trying to tell you.

12:23.462 --> 12:25.484
No one is cheating.
- [sighs]

12:25.584 --> 12:28.047
- Your father and I are...

12:28.147 --> 12:30.930
in an open relationship.

12:31.030 --> 12:32.772
[quirky dramatic music]

12:32.872 --> 12:34.493
- Oh.

12:34.593 --> 12:35.935
It's just an open relationship.

12:36.035 --> 12:37.136
both: Yes.

12:37.236 --> 12:39.779
- [laughing]
Okay, that's great.

12:39.879 --> 12:41.100
- Denise, have some class.

12:41.200 --> 12:43.182
- Okay, all right.

12:43.282 --> 12:44.944
So you're in
an open relationship.

12:45.044 --> 12:47.386
So you're just, like, what,
doing it with other couples?

12:47.486 --> 12:48.627
- [laughing]
No, no, no, of course not.

12:48.727 --> 12:49.909
That's swinging.

12:50.009 --> 12:50.990
- [laughing]
That's a common mistake.

12:51.090 --> 12:52.271
- Look, look, look, Denise.

12:52.371 --> 12:54.874
Your mother and I,
we are very much in love.

12:54.974 --> 12:56.675
- Mm-hmm.

12:56.775 --> 13:01.520
- But we're also on individual
journeys of sexual exploration.

13:01.620 --> 13:02.882
- So when you said that

13:02.982 --> 13:04.443
you were listening
to each other's needs,

13:04.543 --> 13:06.125
you're talking about
those needs?

13:06.225 --> 13:07.727
- And we've met
some very lovely people.

13:07.827 --> 13:08.968
It's not all sexual.
- No, no.

13:09.068 --> 13:11.290
Well, it's mostly sexual.

13:11.390 --> 13:12.691
- It is mostly sexual.

13:12.791 --> 13:13.893
- Please stop saying sexual.

13:13.993 --> 13:15.294
- Okay, fine.
Sensual.

13:15.394 --> 13:16.976
- Oh, that's so much worse.

13:17.076 --> 13:20.179
- Denise, we really didn't
want you to find out this way.

13:20.279 --> 13:22.301
- Or at all.

13:22.401 --> 13:23.702
- I'm gonna go
take a land shower.

13:23.802 --> 13:24.904
- Okay.

13:25.004 --> 13:27.827
[upbeat steel drum music]

13:27.927 --> 13:30.309
♪ ♪

13:30.409 --> 13:31.871
- Rule 12,

13:31.971 --> 13:33.392
you must remain seated
in the hot tub at all times.

13:33.492 --> 13:35.514
Rule 13,
no fingers in the jets.

13:35.614 --> 13:36.956
Rule 14, no splashing.

13:37.056 --> 13:38.317
Rule 15, no laughing.

13:38.417 --> 13:39.759
It could be mistaken
for screaming,

13:39.859 --> 13:41.320
which might cause alarm.

13:41.420 --> 13:43.162
Now, has anyone had diarrhoea
in the past couple weeks?

13:43.262 --> 13:45.124
- Should we just watch a movie?
- Yeah.

13:45.224 --> 13:48.167
- Okay, but you guys
are missing out on rule 16.

13:48.267 --> 13:50.049
Rule 16 is have fun!

13:50.149 --> 13:52.171
- Oh, excuse me.
Can you grab me one, sweetie?

13:52.271 --> 13:53.692
♪ ♪

13:53.792 --> 13:54.974
Left me hanging.

13:55.074 --> 13:56.415
- Wow.

13:56.515 --> 13:59.018
- Sure seems like
we're in hot water with her.

13:59.118 --> 14:01.020
- Jay, now is not the time
for Steve Harvey.

14:01.120 --> 14:02.341
- You're right.

14:02.441 --> 14:03.742
- Although that was clever.
- Thank you.

14:03.842 --> 14:06.425
- Look at them in there.
Disgusting.

14:06.525 --> 14:09.989
- Okay,
emotions are obviously high.

14:10.089 --> 14:11.710
Why don't we try one
of your calming techniques?

14:11.810 --> 14:13.312
Just close your eyes.

14:13.412 --> 14:17.516
Now, imagine you're holding
an energy gem in one hand

14:17.616 --> 14:21.881
and, like, a moonshine
incense crystal in the other.

14:21.981 --> 14:23.963
- Are you making up crystals?

14:24.063 --> 14:25.444
- It's not my area
of expertise.

14:25.544 --> 14:28.487
- I'm going inside.

14:28.587 --> 14:30.409
- I have never
seen her this upset.

14:30.509 --> 14:32.651
I should go talk to her.
- No. I'll do it.

14:32.751 --> 14:34.533
I'm the one
who swiped on her mom.

14:34.633 --> 14:35.614
- Mm.

14:35.714 --> 14:37.696
- Hey, Jay, Tamara.

14:37.796 --> 14:38.898
How those jets treating you?

14:38.998 --> 14:40.379
- Oh, perfect!

14:40.479 --> 14:42.701
- Think I should alert them
to the risk of filter fungus?

14:42.801 --> 14:44.663
- Tom,
it's a two-day-old hot tub.

14:44.763 --> 14:46.425
- Let's keep the hands
above water, guys.

14:46.525 --> 14:48.567
Just for--for fun.
Keep 'em up there!

14:49.448 --> 14:52.071
- Why can't they be like
normal old folk?

14:52.171 --> 14:53.592
They should be telling people
to get off their lawn,

14:53.692 --> 14:55.674
not getting it on
with people on their lawn.

14:55.774 --> 14:56.795
- Are they doing that?

14:56.895 --> 14:58.437
- Probably.
I don't know.

14:58.537 --> 14:59.798
- I know this must be rough,

14:59.898 --> 15:01.560
but you were dreading
them coming here

15:01.660 --> 15:03.322
because of how much
they bicker.

15:03.422 --> 15:05.204
Now they're getting along.
Isn't that better?

15:05.304 --> 15:07.406
- They are driving a sex barge
across the country.

15:07.506 --> 15:08.928
- I get it, okay?

15:09.028 --> 15:10.850
No one wants to picture
their parents doing it,

15:10.950 --> 15:13.412
smashing off the side
of Route 66,

15:13.512 --> 15:15.414
up against the St. Louis Arch,

15:15.514 --> 15:16.936
looking over Niagara Falls,

15:17.036 --> 15:19.939
maybe using the energy
from the Red Rocks to...

15:20.039 --> 15:21.140
really get after--

15:21.240 --> 15:22.381
- Connor.

15:22.481 --> 15:24.583
- Yeah, sorry.
I kinda want an RV.

15:24.683 --> 15:26.785
But the point is they're not
actually hurting anyone.

15:26.885 --> 15:28.948
Unlike when my dad straight up
cheated on my mom

15:29.048 --> 15:30.789
or when Emily cheated on me.

15:30.889 --> 15:32.271
They're just being honest
with each other

15:32.371 --> 15:34.633
and it's making them happy.

15:34.733 --> 15:37.716
Maybe it's possible something
can be weird and pretty gross,

15:37.816 --> 15:40.839
but also not wrong?

15:40.939 --> 15:42.761
- I hate that you're giving me
a lot to think about.

15:42.861 --> 15:45.084
- I know, right?
Not usually my thing.

15:45.184 --> 15:46.445
Hey,
could you actually text Sarah

15:46.545 --> 15:48.407
and tell her I'm being
super smart and sensitive?

15:48.507 --> 15:50.129
[lively music]

15:50.229 --> 15:52.011
- You know what?
I'm getting in there.

15:52.111 --> 15:54.493
- Good for you, honey.
You deserve to enjoy it.

15:54.593 --> 15:55.814
- No, I want to make sure

15:55.914 --> 15:57.096
their suits don't
get sucked into the intake.

15:57.196 --> 15:58.817
Jay's wearing
some baggy trunks.

15:58.917 --> 16:01.020
- Okay, Tom.

16:01.120 --> 16:03.702
The idea was to get something
that would make you happy,

16:03.802 --> 16:05.784
and I'm feeling like
that is not this.

16:05.884 --> 16:07.546
- What are you talking about?
I love the hot tub.

16:07.646 --> 16:09.348
It's so relaxing.

16:09.448 --> 16:11.630
Don't I look relaxed?

16:11.730 --> 16:17.116
♪ ♪

16:17.216 --> 16:18.717
- Okay, fine.

16:18.817 --> 16:19.898
I've been a stress case
since we bought this thing.

16:19.978 --> 16:21.120
What do you want me to say?
I'm miserable.

16:21.220 --> 16:22.922
- So then just return it
and get something else.

16:23.022 --> 16:24.603
- Like what?

16:24.703 --> 16:26.285
A car loses half its value
once you drive it off the lot,

16:26.385 --> 16:27.646
you get a new computer,

16:27.746 --> 16:29.568
boom, they come out
with a better one, and...

16:29.668 --> 16:31.130
I know I'm not cool enough
to pull off a banjo.

16:31.230 --> 16:32.251
- There's gotta be something

16:32.351 --> 16:33.812
that you can
spend that money on.

16:33.912 --> 16:35.214
- What if there's not?

16:35.314 --> 16:37.896
What if I'm incapable
of enjoying myself?

16:37.996 --> 16:39.898
- Massage chair?
- They catch fire.

16:39.998 --> 16:45.884
♪ ♪

16:47.806 --> 16:51.190
- Hey, I saw the truck
from Hot Tub Depot.

16:51.290 --> 16:54.513
- Yup, she's gone.

16:54.613 --> 16:56.615
I don't think that grass
is ever growing back.

16:57.416 --> 16:59.878
- Well, I have been thinking

16:59.978 --> 17:02.041
of ways that
you could use the money.

17:02.141 --> 17:04.163
There's a wizarding camp.

17:04.263 --> 17:05.604
Don't worry.
It's mostly adults.

17:05.704 --> 17:08.607
- No, no, I've--I've given up.

17:08.707 --> 17:09.969
I don't think there's anything

17:10.069 --> 17:11.250
I could buy for myself
that'll make me happy.

17:11.350 --> 17:13.572
- Aw, Tom.
I'm sorry.

17:13.672 --> 17:15.774
- No, it's okay. I know
what I wanna spend the money.

17:15.874 --> 17:18.137
Making you happy.

17:18.237 --> 17:20.139
I want you
to quit your job at the firm

17:20.239 --> 17:21.940
and focus on your
design business full-time.

17:22.040 --> 17:23.742
- Tom, that's crazy.
What?

17:23.842 --> 17:25.944
- What are you talking about?
You did the same thing for me.

17:26.044 --> 17:29.748
I wanna take my book money
and do that for you.

17:29.848 --> 17:31.991
- [sighs]
I mean, that would be amazing,

17:32.091 --> 17:33.552
but the firm is steady work.

17:33.652 --> 17:35.194
The design thing, who knows?

17:35.294 --> 17:37.556
- I do.

17:37.656 --> 17:40.359
You are so talented.

17:40.459 --> 17:42.161
[soft dramatic music]

17:42.261 --> 17:44.883
- Tom, I don't know if I could
let you do that for me.

17:44.983 --> 17:48.087
- Oh, well, this isn't for you.
This is for me.

17:48.187 --> 17:50.289
Yeah, this is totally selfish.

17:50.389 --> 17:52.091
I have this weird thing about

17:52.191 --> 17:54.293
my wife being fulfilled
and not miserable.

17:54.393 --> 17:55.494
It's, like...
- Mm.

17:55.594 --> 17:56.735
- I don't know,
it's kind of my kink.

17:56.835 --> 17:59.538
- Ugh, you sick man.

17:59.638 --> 18:00.739
Thank you.

18:00.839 --> 18:03.702
- See, you,
you're my hot tub.

18:03.802 --> 18:05.464
- Mm.

18:05.564 --> 18:07.946
And you are my filter fungus.

18:08.046 --> 18:09.508
- [chuckling] That's right.

18:09.608 --> 18:10.489
'Cause you're never getting rid
of me.

18:10.569 --> 18:12.791
- Mm-hmm.
[chuckling and smooching]

18:12.891 --> 18:14.153
[soft upbeat music]

18:14.253 --> 18:16.115
Mm.

18:16.215 --> 18:17.596
Mrs. Kim is watching us.

18:17.696 --> 18:19.598
- See, I told you.

18:19.698 --> 18:20.759
- You know what?

18:20.859 --> 18:22.761
Let her.
- All right.

18:22.861 --> 18:27.866
♪ ♪

18:28.787 --> 18:29.968
- Hey.
- Oh, well, hey, baby girl.

18:30.068 --> 18:32.291
- Hey.
- Can we talk?

18:32.391 --> 18:33.292
- Of course.
- Yeah, yeah, yeah.

18:33.392 --> 18:34.333
Come on out.

18:34.433 --> 18:36.055
- Well, we were thinking

18:36.155 --> 18:38.377
the last thing that we want is
for you to feel uncomfortable.

18:38.477 --> 18:39.898
- Yeah, so tomorrow,

18:39.998 --> 18:42.741
we're gonna climb inside Susan
and get out of here.

18:42.841 --> 18:44.383
Susan's what we call the RV.

18:44.483 --> 18:47.025
- Oh, um, no.
You don't have to do that.

18:47.125 --> 18:49.908
I just wanted to apologise
for how I reacted.

18:50.008 --> 18:52.191
That was not my best moment.

18:52.291 --> 18:53.672
- Oh, we understand.

18:53.772 --> 18:55.554
It must've come
as such a shock.

18:55.654 --> 18:56.915
And looking back,

18:57.015 --> 18:59.078
I would say that
my photo with the ice cream

18:59.178 --> 19:00.879
was a little suggestive.

19:00.979 --> 19:03.242
- In mine, I'm holding a banjo.

19:03.342 --> 19:05.444
Which is pretty cool.
[chuckles]

19:05.544 --> 19:07.806
- Well, I also just shouldn't
have been so judgmental.

19:07.906 --> 19:09.848
- No, no, baby.
It's okay.

19:09.948 --> 19:12.851
- No, it's not.
You two never judge me.

19:12.951 --> 19:14.413
Even when I came out as gay

19:14.513 --> 19:17.376
or changed from pre-med
to folklore and mythology.

19:17.476 --> 19:19.258
- Yeah, that was tough.

19:19.358 --> 19:21.180
- All you ever wanted
was for me to be happy,

19:21.280 --> 19:22.381
and I want the same for you.

19:22.481 --> 19:24.783
- Sweetie, we are happy.
We are.

19:24.883 --> 19:27.106
- Yeah,
and we are so proud of you

19:27.206 --> 19:29.468
and the life that
you built here with Sarah.

19:29.568 --> 19:30.829
- Thank you.
- Yeah.

19:30.929 --> 19:32.111
- I love you both.

19:32.211 --> 19:33.272
- We love you.
- Aw, we love you too.

19:33.372 --> 19:35.754
- You know that.
[both chuckle]

19:35.854 --> 19:39.758
- And I can't believe
I'm saying this, but Dad...

19:39.858 --> 19:42.000
- Mm-hmm?

19:42.100 --> 19:44.563
- The banjo's not gonna
get you a lot of swipes.

19:44.663 --> 19:46.445
- I tried to tell him.

19:46.545 --> 19:48.046
- Really?
- Yeah.

19:48.146 --> 19:50.129
- Hey!
- Oh, there he is!

19:50.229 --> 19:53.292
- How was your first
official day as a designer?

19:53.392 --> 19:54.573
- Amazing.

19:54.673 --> 19:57.536
No legal briefs,
no documents redaction.

19:57.636 --> 19:59.778
I wore sneakers.
[both laugh]

19:59.878 --> 20:00.859
- Well, you know what?

20:00.959 --> 20:03.382
If you're happy,
then I'm happy.

20:03.482 --> 20:04.943
And I want you
to know something.

20:05.043 --> 20:06.084
I'm gonna stop
getting in my head so much.

20:06.164 --> 20:08.867
I'm done worrying
about every little thing.

20:08.967 --> 20:09.828
- I love hearing that.

20:09.928 --> 20:11.470
Ooh, also

20:11.570 --> 20:12.651
I met this new contractor
that I'm gonna partner with.

20:12.731 --> 20:14.032
Come meet him.
- What, he's here right now?

20:14.132 --> 20:15.634
- Mm-hmm.
- Oh, cool.

20:15.734 --> 20:18.357
[dramatic saxophone sting]

20:18.457 --> 20:19.438
What the hell?

20:19.538 --> 20:21.680
- Hey, I'm Santiago.

20:21.780 --> 20:23.602
- Hey, I'm Tom.

20:23.702 --> 20:26.004
- Also known as the man
who brought us together.

20:26.104 --> 20:29.568
- Oh. [chuckles]
I-I wouldn't say that.

20:29.668 --> 20:31.450
- I would. I mean,
if it wasn't for you, this...

20:31.550 --> 20:32.931
[clicks tongue]
Wouldn't be happening.

20:33.031 --> 20:35.694
- So what exactly, uh,
is happening?

20:35.794 --> 20:39.057
- Thank you so much for making
your wife available to me.

20:39.157 --> 20:42.941
- [chuckling weakly]
Well, she's all yours.

20:43.041 --> 20:45.504
I love that I did this.

20:45.604 --> 20:47.606
So great.

20:49.488 --> 20:50.709
- No ice cream, no candy,
no gum in the tub.

20:50.809 --> 20:51.710
In fact, you know what?

20:51.810 --> 20:53.111
No sugary substances at all,

20:53.211 --> 20:54.833
unless you have
a medical issue, which--

20:54.933 --> 20:56.635
yeah, you can come
tell me about privately.

20:56.735 --> 20:57.996
What else?
Okay, rule number nine.

20:58.096 --> 20:59.478
Guys, no politics, okay?

20:59.578 --> 21:01.720
Weather talk is allowed,
even encouraged.

21:01.820 --> 21:03.121
Speaking of which,

21:03.221 --> 21:04.923
you should all
be on the lookout for storms.

21:05.023 --> 21:07.706
Remember,
precipitation equals...

21:09.668 --> 21:11.009
Evacuation.

21:11.109 --> 21:13.452
